I can't remember a place with a better soufflÃ©, so I am just going say Gary Danko has the best souffle. There are many Michelin star restaurants with good food in the area, but some of them don't quite live up to the standard in my opinion. This problem can mostly be attributed to subpar service. My boyfriend and I were visiting home one weekend and decided to make a stop here for a date night. He called on a Thursday night and got reservations for 9 on Saturday night. We were running a little late and couldn't find parking. When Gary Danko called, I explained our situation and the hostess was very friendly and kindly told me that our table would be waiting for us when we arrived. What I really enjoyed/appreciated about Gary Danko was how SUPERB their service was. Every waiter/waitress had smiles on their faces making the atmosphere very warm and welcoming (we expected it to have a bougie feeling, as most high-end restaurants we've gone to do). They were patient and gladly helped us while making our choices. We both opted for the three-course meal because it was such a late dinner and we both didn't want to stuff ourselves before going out that night. Another great thing about GD is how CUSTOMIZABLE the menu is. You can choose ANY 3,4, or 5 items you want, depending on how many courses you choose, so everyone and their bellies leave happy! Risotto (5/5): Easily, my FAVORITE dish of the night. The risotto lives up to its hype, and it's easy to see why. It was cooked to perfection and each succeeding bite tasted BETTER and BETTER! So creamy and rich, and the crab was cooked perfectly. You MUST get this! Roast Maine Lobster (4.5/5): I hesitated to order this dish because I thought it would be such a small portion, but much to my surprise, it was a good size. I had two pieces of sweet and succulent lobster over this creamy potato puree. The lobster was cooked perfectly as well- not rubbery at all! Towards the end of this dish, it did get a little too rich for my taste, but hey, that's just me. Lemon Pepper Duck Breast (4/5): This was probably my least favorite dish of the night. I thought it was good, but nothing too special. The seasoning was great but the middle parts lacked flavor. BUT, the breast was well-cooked and tender. Petit Fours (5/5): After our meal we were brought out petit fours (I'm assuming everyone gets this because the table next to us got it as well) and they were SOO GOOD! Perfect little bite-sized desserts that weren't overpoweringly sweet and the perfect end to a great meal. AND they gave us this DELICIOUS banana bread cake to take home. It was moist and just the right amount of sweetness. Overall, the value for the amount of food you get at Gary Danko, along with their service, is well-worth the experience.

    My boyfriend and I were visiting home one weekend and decided to make a stop here for a date night. He called on a Thursday night and got reservations for 9 on Saturday night. We were running a little late and couldn't find parking. When Gary Danko called, I explained our situation and the hostess was very friendly and kindly told me that our table would be waiting for us when we arrived.

    What I really enjoyed/appreciated about Gary Danko was how SUPERB their service was. Every waiter/waitress had smiles on their faces making the atmosphere very warm and welcoming (we expected it to have a bougie feeling, as most high-end restaurants we've gone to do). They were patient and gladly helped us while making our choices.

    We both opted for the three-course meal because it was such a late dinner and we both didn't want to stuff ourselves before going out that night. Another great thing about GD is how CUSTOMIZABLE the menu is. You can choose ANY 3,4, or 5 items you want, depending on how many courses you choose, so everyone and their bellies leave happy!

    Risotto (5/5): Easily, my FAVORITE dish of the night. The risotto lives up to its hype, and it's easy to see why. It was cooked to perfection and each succeeding bite tasted BETTER and BETTER! So creamy and rich, and the crab was cooked perfectly. You MUST get this!

    Roast Maine Lobster (4.5/5): I hesitated to order this dish because I thought it would be such a small portion, but much to my surprise, it was a good size. I had two pieces of sweet and succulent lobster over this creamy potato puree. The lobster was cooked perfectly as well- not rubbery at all! Towards the end of this dish, it did get a little too rich for my taste, but hey, that's just me.

    Lemon Pepper Duck Breast (4/5): This was probably my least favorite dish of the night. I thought it was good, but nothing too special. The seasoning was great but the middle parts lacked flavor. BUT, the breast was well-cooked and tender.

    Petit Fours (5/5): After our meal we were brought out petit fours (I'm assuming everyone gets this because the table next to us got it as well) and they were SOO GOOD! Perfect little bite-sized desserts that weren't overpoweringly sweet and the perfect end to a great meal. AND they gave us this DELICIOUS banana bread cake to take home. It was moist and just the right amount of sweetness.

    Overall, the value for the amount of food you get at Gary Danko, along with their service, is well-worth the experience.

    First time here for chef Hubby's BDay....service is IMPECCABLE and the food was outstanding!!!! We both got 3 courses - I got the crispy fried egg, duck, and the lemon souffle cake. He got the quail, lamb, and praline. Everything was outstanding. Your glass is never empty and everyone is incredibly knowledgable and helpful.

    I had never had a crispy fried egg, before - it is poached, then panko breaded and fried. It was delicious and perfectly cooked. As was everything else on the plate - the grits were creamy and complementary. Dinner was off to a wonderful start!

    My duck was moist and well-seasoned; the sauces were very good. The duck hash with pancetta was salty and crunchy and a nice texture contrast to the braised endive.

    The lemon souffle cake is incredible...it is the softest, fluffiest textured cake and literally disintegrates as soon as it hits your tongue. It was delicious - not too tart, and the accompanying raspberry sorbet was Â very good as well.

    My husband likewise thoroughly enjoyed everything that he got, as well...as a matter of fact, he cleaned every plate!!! It was his birthday so he also got a chocolate souffle and an array of small plate petit desserts. Even the mocha I had with dessert was great!

    The sommeliers are also very knowledgable and offer great suggestions...the drink "binder" is a little overwhelming, but there's always someone standing by to offer suggestions based on your preferences.

    it was a great BDay experience, and well worth every penny. Very reasonably priced compared to "regular" restaurants, and you cannot beat the service and attention to detail, here. Even the way they serve water and put plates on the table was well thought out!

    We'll definitely be back to try other things on the menu!!!
